So, with the 3rd jamcon theme, I realized we could delve a bit more into strange/unsettling territory, so here's my take.

This SCP is my love letter to Local 58 and similar obscure, unsettling alien-based horror out there. They just keep proving that it doesn't matter how overdone a certain idea is, you can still do it in a cool and original way if you try hard enough.

Fellow human persons who gave their human feedback on this:  DrAkimoto.

Image attribution goes something like this: two. The images were edited by me.





